      <title>VP - Good example of disconnect between players &amp; designers</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&amp;message.id=235564#M235564</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Played around in VP today.&amp;nbsp; This zone, while never really that popular, is pretty&amp;nbsp; much a tomb 24/7.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Why is that?&amp;nbsp; Let's look...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- 3 to 4% AA per kill on the blue trash (solo)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Loot...coin from 1 gp to 9 pp&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Drops?&amp;nbsp; rare and no trade mostly&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Cash drops?&amp;nbsp; Only thing I saw was a basilisk hide...fetched 1pp at the vendor&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Adds...I don't think the zone designer could have packed more mobs in the hallways if they tried&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Key quest to get in the zone, which is okay....if there is some sort of reward for the effort...which there isn't&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;With the exception of a few quests that ppl w/ROV faction may wanna mess with (and these items were obsoleted like 2 expansions ago) this zone is pointless.&amp;nbsp; At least, before it was revamped, it had a few unique Kunark era items that made it worth visiting to fill up your "toy" bags.&amp;nbsp; I don't recall anyone asking for this zone to be revamped, please correct me if I'm wrong.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;What I don't understand, is why can the original Verant team that designed Antonica zones...create zones that still draw players and revamped zones / new expansions get ditched as soon as new content comes around?&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I think some of the dev team actually plays EQ, but it just seems like there is a huge disconnect between what players want and the content that is provided to us.&amp;nbsp; Work and resources go into redesigning zones that are active for 2 weeks...and then go barren.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The only thing I can suggest, is that people who do actual zone designs...get some player input on test servers.&amp;nbsp; I don't know what the criteria would be for said players, but needless to say they should be long time players.&amp;nbsp; Some general criteria, that would at least attract me to&amp;nbsp;a zone, would be...&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1 - XP&amp;nbsp; If they mobs don't give 10% solo AA +, it's not worth my time if XP is what I'm after.&amp;nbsp; This is a good bar because it makes it worthwhile for groups&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;2 - Zones which have mobs packed into every last inch and pulls are a constant train fight...gonna pass on those&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;3 - Zones that have no safe spot to set up a camp to XP in, or med safely in....cross off the list&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;4 - Zones that are itemized with drops that I can sell to other players (gear) are a big plus.&amp;nbsp; An even bigger plus is there are no required limits (we love our twinks)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;5 - Zones that are itemized with unique clickies, or are part of a quest that yields a nice clickie, are on the list.&amp;nbsp; XP is irrelevant (ex:&amp;nbsp; Wood Elf Illusion click mask)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;6 - Zones that require me to camp keys and/or flags should have some sort of tangible benefit...ie VP being a better than average source for blue diamonds, or XP per kill, or coin per kill...there are a few mobs here that drop some tradeskill items, but they are somewhat in the zone and the nature of VP is such that it's just not condusive to farming&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;7 - Zones that have static named camps are favorites of those who like to farm, group or single&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;8 - Zones that can support groups or solo artists are also favorites&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Anyway, just my thoughts.&amp;nbsp; If I'm full of hooie please enlighten me.&amp;nbsp; But IMO, VP is a garbage zone atm.&amp;nbsp; I'd rather see it reverted back to what it was before.&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
