&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/BLOCKQUOTE&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;I understand your reasoning, but being from a guild that has passed that point I had to run thorugh the old key quest on my own to be able to zone in and then had that taken away from me.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;My guild isn't going to take down the dragon to 1) re-flag me, 2) re-flag anyone else (if there is anyone else) 3) flag anyone that has done the "other" access options - again if there is anyone else&amp;nbsp;4) for quest loot that is below what&amp;nbsp;is dropping now.&amp;nbsp; And I have looked for other guilds doing this and have yet to 1) find any or 2) be online when there is a guild doing it.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Perhaps it is just me, but I dislike having something taken away from me for what seems to be an "Arbitrary" decision.&amp;nbsp; You felt that "under the old key quest, getting access to an elemental planes level zone (in terms of difficulty and reward via exp/loot) would have been too easy" so you introduced a raid required mob for access.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;MPG Trials only require a single group and drop better loot.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;A variety of OoW/DoD Rares that can be duoed, drop better loot.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/LI&gt;&#xD;
&lt;LI&gt;Quests rewards in PoR that can be duoed and soloed offer better loot.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/UL&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Point is, trying to get&amp;nbsp;a raid together for the sole fact of getting myself re-keyed (since what does it offer to anyone else in my guild) is fruitless.&amp;nbsp; Perhaps it is time to allow the old key re-entry on its own merits (just don't give it the Augment Change without doing the raid).&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Will this give new life to this zone?&amp;nbsp; Doubt it, but then I am probably in the minority on this one.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
